jobpost:
1010data travels at the speed of thought to make Big Data discovery easy; we power sub second responses to analyses run on billions of rows of data.
An essential tool to more than 750 of the world&rsquo;s top retail, manufacturing, telecom, government and financial services enterprises including The New York Stock Exchange, Dollar General, P&amp;G, and RiteAid; 1010data is a highly differentiated product that is becoming the industry standard for Big Data Discovery and Data Sharing.
We are seeking a Full Stack Developer to automate the process of creating and maintaining large server farms and managing cloud computing.
With more than&nbsp;25 trillion rows of data in our private cloud, 1010data is designed to scale to the largest volumes of granular data, the most disparate and varied data sets, and the most complex advanced analytics. All while delivering lightning-quick system performance.&nbsp;
The Full Stack Developer will be responsible for building, scaling and maintaining our network and server infrastructure as we grow thousands of customers and automate the management of back-end development.
We are so successful because we are the fastest. The fastest. We are already working on superfast computers and need you to make them faster; migrate our existing Windows fleet to Linux while obsessing over performance optimization.
You will be developing adaptive distributed system software and high-speed communication system software to support high-performance distributed computing (HPDC) applications. If it&rsquo;s not fast, we are not interested.&nbsp;
If you are passionate about hardware and software you will work with top of the line products to will improve our performance. &nbsp;Our engineers possess a unique mix of programming and systems expertise who love solving problems most don&rsquo;t like to think about.&nbsp;
At 1010data experience in a specific programming language is&nbsp;not&nbsp;required; however the right person knows&nbsp;how&nbsp;to program and will learn new languages quickly.
Overall you should have a strong, general knowledge of technical infrastructure and how and why things work together.&nbsp; You should also demonstrate a solid, analytical thought process in response to challenges or problems.&nbsp;
If you value the power of driving strategic vendor decisions and are confident in embracing new technologies to tackle our high volume, scalable problems we would like to speak with you!
Responsibilities: &nbsp;

Scale production systems, develop new features, and fix bugs on massive distributed frameworks&nbsp;
Reliability, performance tuning and scalability of High Performance and Distributed computer systems &nbsp;
Building the core components of our system &nbsp;
Set the technical direction of our solution &nbsp;
Architect latest in performance enhancements &nbsp;

Requirements:&nbsp;
Education and Experience:

STEM degree from top tier university preferred; Mathematics, Statics oriented and HPDC course work highly desired&nbsp;
2+ years of proven&nbsp;experience&nbsp;managing exotic or custom environments is critical. &nbsp;
Experience in HPC
Rotational work after hours or weekends.

Skills:

Solid multi threaded, concurrent and&nbsp;socket-level&nbsp;programming skills&nbsp;are&nbsp;crucial&nbsp;
Algorithm design for Systems scalability of Parallel and Distributed Systems;
Solid understanding of algorithms for performance tuning; debugging familiar with tools such as Valgrind to optimize code, memory use performance etc.
Familiarity with&nbsp;Functional/Vector programming including any of the following ideal K, APL, Erlang, Haskell, J, Lisp, Scheme, Ocaml, Q, Scala would be nice&nbsp;
Software engineering for HA/DR

Management requirements:

Previous management experience is not necessary for this position but there is opportunity for growth and advancement.

Personal Competencies:&nbsp;
Personal Impact:

The successful person will be a cooperative, creative person who is strongly motivated to solve business issues.&nbsp; This person will be adept at finding the right technology balance to solve problems quickly and efficiently, while creating a maintainable codebase that can evolve as technologies change. This person must be capable of working independently and towards goals vs. just following instructions. &nbsp;&nbsp;

Communication:

communicate clearly and have strong, positive interpersonal skills;
feel comfortable presenting to a group including management;
have the ability to articulate in his/her ideas, consider options presented by others and reach an informed, balanced technical opinion;
create clear, concise memos/summaries, design documentation and presentations
demonstrate the ability to review the technical documentation provided by others and provide constructive comments.

